{\plain \fs20 \b\fs20 [PREFACE TO THE MODERN LITERAL VERSION]}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 2015 Update}{\plain \fs20 \b\fs20 \par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \par
}{\plain \fs20 \b\fs20 Quick Overview:}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 The {\u8220\'93}Modern Literal Version{\u8221\'94} uses the Majority Text ({\u8220\'93}The New Testament in the Original Greek Byzantine Textform \softline
2005 Compiled and Arranged by Maurice A. Robinson and William Pierpont{\u8221\'94}).\par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 Two distinct and opposite techniques are used in translating the New Testament from the Greek. The "Modern Literal \softline
Version" is the first type, a {\u8216\'91}literal' translation sometimes called {\u8216\'91}word-for-word' translation. The second and most \softline
common in the past 30 years is to paraphrase the Greek into English. These are: dynamic equivalence, free style, thought-for-thought , better than a word-for-word and so on.  We understand the value of paraphrases for those looking for a \softline
Bible that reads as easily as a newspaper, however we feel strongly about having a Bible without opinions of what was \softline
meant but instead faithfully reproduces the original Greek Bible into Modern English. One way to look at this is: if there \softline
was a court case with a particular document that was being used as evidence and this document was in a foreign language \softline
would a "thought-for-thought" translation be acceptable?  The {\u8216\'91}document' we are talking about here is the {\u8216\'91}Last Will and \softline
Testament' of our Lord Jesus & Savior. The goal of everyone who worked on the "Modern Literal Version" was to keep \softline
any form of commentary or paraphrase out of this translation as is humanly possible. The MLV is not sold for profit \softline
because there is no denomination or publishing company or foundation behind it. All Christian groups have had the \softline
opportunity to submit fixes or help. The only uninspired traditions kept in the MLV are: punctuation and capitalization; \softline
chapter and verse numbers; and book order.\par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \par
}{\plain \fs20 \b\fs20 The Open Translation Bible:}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 The Modern Literal Version Bible is considered {\u8216\'91}finished,{\u8217\'92} although it has been open for revision by anyone since 1998. \softline
Our utmost desire is to have a translation that has no errors and }{\plain \fs20 \fs20 we believe that the best way to produce an error-free \softline
translation is to keep it open to the public in the same manner as {\u8216\'91}open-source software{\u8217\'92} is to programmers. We have \softline
found no better way than our {\u8216\'91}open translation{\u8217\'92} idea in its 15 years to achieve this goal. }{\plain \fs20 \fs20 Absolutely anyone in the world \softline
is able to contribute, for sure, the few million who have visited the Christian Library have had that opportunity. You, too, \softline
may make recommendations or help with the entire New Testament, with either Greek or English type proofreading. If \softline
the recommendations this next year warrant another update next year, we will do one }{\plain \fs20 \fs20 per year in printed form & Kindle. \softline
If they are simply 20 places that need corrected, we will provide a corrections list on the web site to update printed books. \softline
We plan to update free electronic versions periodically throughout the year if needed. The {\u8216\'91}cutting edge{\u8217\'92} update is always \softline
the }{\plain \fs20 \b\fs20 BOLD}{\plain \fs20 \fs20  Letter Edition PDF at http://www.ModernLiteralVersion.org/bibles/MLV/MLVBL.pdf \par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 As far as we know, this 'open translation' idea is unique to the MLV and you are invited to participate in helping to make \softline
the MLV even better. There is even a Facebook group at https://www.facebook.com/groups/MLVbible. }{\plain \fs20 \fs20 All who have \softline
helped, have contributed something to further the readability or accuracy of this translation or simply double checked \softline
all who have worked on this translation before them. It is time the Bible is back into the hands of every day Christians, \softline
not some big publishing company only out to make money. Any corrections please email to mlvbible (at) gmail (dot) \softline
com with subject line: {\u8220\'93}MLV{\u8221\'94}.\par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \par
