}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \tab 1. A }{\plain \fs20 \b\fs20 denarius }{\plain \fs20 \fs20 was equivalent to a day's wage of the normal working class. It was a silver coin with Caesar's \softline
face on it. G1220.\par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \tab 2. Two drachmas was worth about 4 denarius, translated as {\u8216\'91}four-denarius.{\u8217\'92} G1323.\par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \tab 3. A lepton was a bronze coin, translated as {\u8216\'91}bronze-coin.{\u8217\'92} Two of these is equal to an Assarion or Quadran \softline
