because of tradition, for example {\u8216\'91}Satan{\u8217\'92} is {\u8216\'91}The Adversary{\u8217\'92} and {\u8216\'91}angel{\u8217\'92} is now {\u8216\'91}messenger{\u8217\'92} (a serious issue because \softline
people didn't know 'messenger' and 'angel' are from the same Greek word), etc.\par
}\pard \fs20\qj\tx0\tx1134\tx2268\tx3402\tx4536\tx5670\tx6804\tx7938\tx9072 
{\plain \fs20 \fs20 G. This is probably the best translation anyone could use if studying Greek, because of its uniformity.\par
