{\plain \fs20 \fs20 The English language has 450,000 base words of which could be used to translate the 5401 Greek words of which \softline
make up the Greek New Testament. About 630 Bible Greek words actually have more than one meaning even after \softline
careful consideration of which English word to substitute; the context determines which meaning is used. Of the \softline
5401 different Greek words, 1877 only occur once, 589 are proper names, 1450 are compounds of two words that \softline
should be translated the same or very similarly as if the two words were not in compound or contracted form. }{\plain \fs20 \fs20 No \softline
language can be treated purely like a math equation but the MLV tried.\par
}\pard \fs20\qj\tx-2188\tx-1055\tx79\tx1213\tx2347\tx3481\tx4615\tx5749\tx6883 
{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \par
