{\plain \fs20 \fs20 The following list requires a Greek Interlinear to look up the corresponding Greek word. (H) denotes the word is \softline
a Helper word which is used to express tense, mood, direction, intensity, person and such. (WG) is a Word Group, \softline
one base word and 1 or more of its compounds. (1,2,3, etc) is just the number of Greek words this English word \softline
renders. Ones in BOLD have no Greek counterpart (just Helper words). Even with 450,000 English words, English \softline
just doesn{\u8217\'92}t have enough synonyms for everyone of the 5401 Greek words. (Sorry, this list is not finished with all \softline
the explanations, i.e. (... ) sections.)\par
